																								 New Delhi, Nov. 28: ONGC Videsh Ltd, the overseas arm of state-run Oil amp; Natural Gas Corporation, has won two oil exploration blocks in Brazil  a deepwater block 470 in Espirito Santo Basin and a shallow water block 1413 in Santos Basin. A consortia led by Petrobras and Perenco had also bid for the block 470, while Petrobras and Ecopetrol submitted bids for the block 1413, ONGC said in a statement. Winning companies offered about $1.2 billion as signature bonus, which has created a record, the company said in a statement.																								 New Delhi, Nov. 28: The board of approval for special economic zones (SEZ) will meet on December 12 to consider 36 proposals, including those by state-run steel firm sail, real estate firm dlf and drug maker Dr Reddys Laboratories. The meeting was scheduled for tomorrow.																								 New Delhi, Nov. 28: External affairs minister Pranab Mukherjee will head the group of ministers (GoM) constituted to look into the pricing of petroleum products.																								 Mumbai, Nov. 28: Futures trading in oil has been banned in eight securities, including Reliance Petroleum, Essar Oil and Bongaigaon Refinery. Derivative contracts in these companies have crossed 95 per cent of market-wide position limit and any fresh position has been banned.																								 Mumbai, Nov. 28: Software solutions company Mastek has received the shareholders approval for buyback of its equity shares at a price not exceeding Rs 750 per share.																								 Mumbai, Nov. 28: Indiabulls Financial Services three promoters  Sameer Gehlaut, Saurabh Mittal and Rajiv Rattan  have raised their shareholding in the company by purchasing shares worth Rs 375 crore.																								 Mumbai, Nov. 28: Kirloskar Electric Companys board has approved the de-merger of the operating business of Kirloskar Power Equipment.
